                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-248-off1328 t18310407-248-crimeloc1330"></join>, and is a <rs id="t18310407-248-viclabel1331" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-248-victim1723 t18310407-248-viclabel1331"></join>. On the Saturday before the 28th of February I was in the shop, and saw the prisoner about for a quarter of an hour; I went into my back parlour, to my little girl, who had fallen down, and on coming into the shop again, I missed these articles - the trousers had been on the doorpost, and the breeches near the door; I had put them there not long before - I went out, and missed the prisoner; I went in again, and sat down some time, when I thought I saw him on the other side of the way, with a bundle under his arm- I looked, and saw the strings and buttons of the smallclothes hanging out of the bundle; I called the Policeman, who ran, and took him - these are the articles; the breeches are worth 7s. 2d. and the trousers 6s. 3d.</p>
               <p>
            
